brewery.brewery_description:
Flamin Galah Brewing Co was founded in 2018 by owners Sam and Claire Hewson, who were both born and bred in Jervis Bay NSW.

Quality over quantity, respect for the industry and a genuine approach are all things Claire and Sam stand for. Their personal experience has been documented on youtube during the difficult task of opening a microbrewery. 2021 is set to be a big year with plans to open their own brewpub in their hometown of Huskisson.

Currently Flamin Galah have a core range of six different craft beers that they're retailing from the small tap room they created one week after opening in March 2020 (right before a global pandemic was announced).

beer.beer_description:
Gold Medalist 2022 awarded by Independent Beer Awards 2022.

Brewed to style, this XPA is has flavours of citrus, passionfruit and caramel.

Lose Zulu time, like a pilot at the yoke, with a skin full. An undercarriage of choc flavour and a crosswind of lime and stone fruits.

Wai-iti & galaxy hops with a dash of choc malt.

Light tropical and citrus flavours

Hopped with citra and galaxy hops.

Gold Medalist in the 2022 Independent Beer awards
this is an incredible Juicy/Hazy Pale Ale, brewed to style perfectly. 
Packed full of flavours of melon, pineapple, tropical and citrus flavours.

Take off with this IPA engineered like a well oiled spaceship. Deploying a pungent eclipse of earth and citrus. Houston, we've got a drinking problem.

Hopped with cascade, galaxy and Columbus giving this a bitter grapefruit, spice and herbal finish, leaving you wanting more.
A beautifully crafted summer ale with low bitterness and tropical flavours from Saaz, Eldorado, Galaxy, Mosaic, Citra hops. Very approachable and easy drinking.

Like a half cut sensei after championships this IPA commands attention. Fly kicking your tastebuds with a  physical assault of peaches and apricot, finishing you off with a citrus roundhouse.

Malty, stonefruit and lime flavours from wai-iti hops
A crisp, clean and refreshing German style beer. Easy drinking with hops of Saaz and Chinook. Its our recommendation for not-so-crafty drinkers.
A malty, smooth beer with lime, peachy and apricot fruit flavours. Hopped with Galaxy, Chinook and Wai-iti.
A black IPA with dark, chocolate roasted malts and hopped with cascade,galaxy and Columbus hops. Smooth toffee, choc and coffee flavours
Roasted barley, Caramunich malt for that caramel flavour and scorched fresh orange skins, twice infused. In the boil & during active fermentation.

Hypnotise your cobra with our Pink City Raspberry Ale. Blushing with ruby terracotta hues, hopped with Eldorado, Citra and Columbus, this ale fuses together a chandelier of flavours of ripe raspberry, soft melon and citrus. Fermented with fresh raspberries not artificial raspberry flavouring.

Originating from one of our grandmothers Christmas treats, this lattice biscuit stout has sticky vanilla and caramel flavours complimented buy a grain bill of dark specialty roasted malts including biscuit malt, giving it a biscuit, chocolate and coffee aroma. Finished with organic vanilla beans and vanilla pudding sugar.
American IPA, highly dry hopped with Citra, Eldorado and galaxy hops. A clear, fruity, Juicy IPA.
Bitter, Pear, Herbal, Pine, Hopped El Dorado & Mosaic
